LAKE AT NO WAKE DUE TO SIGNIFICANT RAIN FALL
LAKE TESTED AFTER SIGNIFICANT RAIN FALL AND NO WAKE FOR 2 WEEKS
THIS WAS ONLY A TEST NOT REAL DATA

When I previously entered the data- the screens for Mill Lake and Green Lake somehow got intermingled.  When I was entering the data for Mill Lake- I noticed that the heading in the upper RH corner said "Green Lake"- yet I was in the Mill lake data entry screen. The secchi data for Mill lake ended up in the Green lake screen- so I'm re-entering the correct secchi data.
Windy and choppy. It was difficult at times to see the disc due to the waves. Air temp 66F- sunny and windy.

Became cloudy as I traveled from Mill Lake to Green. Green lake was very windy and the water was extremely choppy with a strong east wind. I repeated this test 6 times as the secchi readings seemed abnormally low.  Perhaps the readings were a result of the drop in sunlight and higher winds.
Moderate wind (out of the east)- more chop than Mill Lake and overcast.
sunny- slight chop- wind was switching around while we were testing- definite algae bloom
Lake was busy all week  and the water was very choppy. Daytime high temps were in the upper 80's. Definite algae bloom.
Had problems with the HACH meter. The screen fogged up and we couldn't read the temperatures. I was able to correct the problem by warming the meter and drying it out.
